<item>
            <title>[PDFBOX-1069] Ubuntu throws exceptions when fonts missing</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-1069</link>
                <project id="12310760" key="PDFBOX">PDFBox</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On a plain vanilla Ubuntu 10.10 install, running&lt;br/&gt;
run-all failed to render any text, and threw lots of exceptions:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        org.apache.pdfbox.pdmodel.font.PDTrueTypeFont.getawtFont(PDTrueTypeFont.java:425)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;...however, installing the package &quot;ttf-mscorefonts-installer&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
made those exceptions go away.&lt;br/&gt;
(ubuntu1010_output.txt shows the exceptions; ubuntu1010_try2_output.txt is a run after the extra fonts are installed)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Might be able to fix this one by setting UNKNOWN_FONT in&lt;br/&gt;
Resources/PDFBox_External_Fonts.properties, but it would seem like&lt;br/&gt;
it should choose some reasonable default if it isn&apos;t set...&lt;br/&gt;
shouldn&apos;t it?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
